'''Alfred Ritscher''' (23 May 1879 in [[Bad Lauterberg]] - 30 March 1963 in [[Hamburg]]) was a [[Germans|German]] [[polar explorer]]. A [[Captain (naval)|captain]] in the [[German Navy]], he led the third German Antarctic Expedition in 1938-39, which mapped the [[New Swabia]] ({{lang-de|Neuschwabenland}}) area of [[Queen Maud Land]]. [[Ritscher Peak]]<ref name=gnis12867>USGS Geographic Names Information System: [http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/f?p=gnispq:5:::NO::P5_ANTAR_ID:12687 USGS GNIS: Ritscher Peak]</ref> and [[Ritscher Upland]]<ref name=gnis12688>USGS Geographic Names Information System: [http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/f?p=gnispq:5:::NO::P5_ANTAR_ID:12688 USGS GNIS: Ritscher Upland]</ref> there are named for him.
